I made this recipe for a friend of mine who, being a long-time confirmed bachelor, eats most every meal in restaurants--good restaurants. After tasting the steak and asparagus declared "This is better than The Palm!" Enough said. On my way to the kitchen to make it again, yum!

Rating: 4
Made this for dinner tonight. Didn't have oyster sauce so substitued fish sauce, added 2 tsp. of honey and 3 cloves minced garlic. I let the flank steak marinade in the glaze overnight as another reviewer suggested. I did not marinade the asparagus in the glaze, I just poured the remaining glaze from the flank steak prior to cooking. The steak had amazing flavor (my wife said it reminded her of mongolian bbq) and was very tender. Our kids (3 & 5) ate all their portions, had seconds and the youngest even had thirds!

Rating: 4
how does this not have more reviews? Wow. exceptional flavor, surprising for the few and seemingly unrelated ingredients in the marinade. I made just the steak and it was fantastic. I used about a TBS grainy mustard, patted the meat dry-ish after marinating and sprinkled with salt and pepper. slice as thin and on the grain as possible.... addictive flavor....

Rating: 4
AMAZING!! This has become one of our favorite meals! I tripled the glaze recipe and used it as a marinade instead of a glaze. I let the steak marinate overnight, then I baked it in the oven at 350 for about 25-30 minutes (maybe less, I didn't actually time it). So tender!! I also subsituted worchestire sauce and a bit of Splenda for the oyster sauce to cut out some fat and carbs. Delicious!!!

